HEADWORD: Topsoiling
<hw>Top"soil`ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Engin.)</fld> <def>The act or
art of taking off the top soil of land before an excavation or
embankment is begun.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

